com.complexible.common.cache
Class LRUCache<K,V>

java.lang.Object
  com.complexible.common.cache.LRUCache<K,V>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cache<K,V>
Direct Known Subclasses:
CountLimitedLRUCache, SpaceLimitedLRUCache
public abstract class LRUCache<K,V>
extends Object
implements Cache<K,V>

A simple implementation of Guava cache interface using a LinkedHashMap. This implementation is also thread-safe but only because all functions are synchronized so it is not expected to be useful for highly concurrent scenarios. It also provides much less functionality (no soft/weak keys/values, no built-in stats calculation, etc.). The memory usage of this implementation is supposedly less than Guava native implementations but it is not clear how much. In summary, this class might be useful for testing purposes but not a good alternative otherwise.
